title: An investigation of the fission of U-238 and Bi-209 by 1-GeV protons

x4freetext: An investigation of the fission of U-238 and Bi-209
by 1-GeV protons
In Russian.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.17, p.498 (1973)

x4freetext: In English.
The targets were prepared by vacuum deposition on a
100 mu-g/cm2 substrate. The target areas were 0.75 cm2
Surface barrier counters mounted on movable
arms inside the chamber. The working area
of the detectors was 3.5 cm2
synchrocyclotron defined a beam with
0.20 angular spread, 12 mm diameter and 0.5 x 10**10
protons/sec intensity at the target
Statistical method of Monte-Carlo.
The target thicknesses were determined,
with 7% accuracy, by measuring the energy losses of
alpha particles and fission fragments from Cf52
from figs.4,5 of YF,17,950,1973
Last checking has been done.
DATE is corrected
SD: ref. on transl.corrected; corrected
according last EXFOR rules; SF6=AKE/DA changed to KE,
SF7=FF deleted, SF5=PRE and SF8=MSC added to REACTION
code in Subents 2-4. SF7=FF was added to REACTION code
in Subents 5-7.
